The paper also discusses the use of abstractions and approximation algorithms, which are techniques commonly used in the sub-categories cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). 

The paper also mentions the use of reachability properties, which are commonly studied in the sub-category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). 

Finally, the paper discusses the analysis of stochastic timed automata and generalized semi-Markov processes, which are models commonly used in the sub-category cs.SY (Systems and Control). 

Therefore, the likely sub-categories are cs.LO, cs.MA, cs.PL, cs.DS, and cs.SY, ordered from most to least likely.
